================================================================================
STAR RECORD #9
================================================================================

ID: 6a9d2f48-5c7e-4b3a-9e1f-8d4c6b2a7e53

COMPANY: DAYPAIO GmbH
ROLE TITLE: Senior Software Engineer Full Stack - Tech Lead
PERIOD: 2019–2020

DOMAIN AREAS:
CRM • SaaS • Event-Driven Architecture • Full-Stack Development • CQRS

BACKGROUND CONTEXT:
DAYPAIO was building a new CRM platform from scratch to enter the competitive SaaS market. As a startup, speed-to-market was critical, but the architecture needed to be scalable from day one. The cross-functional SCRUM team needed technical leadership to drive architectural decisions, establish coding standards, and deliver a production-ready platform within aggressive market launch deadlines.

SITUATION:
Startup developing greenfield CRM platform requiring end-to-end architecture, modern scalable design, and rapid market delivery. Team lacked established architectural patterns, coding standards, and testing practices. Needed technical leadership to design robust foundation while maintaining startup velocity.

TASK:
Spearhead end-to-end architecture, development, and market launch of CRM platform as Tech Lead within cross-functional SCRUM team. Design highly scalable, event-driven microservices using modern patterns and technologies, establish front-end standards, champion testing practices, and mentor junior engineers.

ACTIONS:
• Designed event-driven RESTful microservices architecture using NestJS (TypeScript) and EventStore
• Implemented CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation) pattern to optimize scalability and performance for read/write workloads
• Architected event sourcing infrastructure for complete audit trails and temporal queries
• Led front-end development using Angular 9, establishing reusable component design standards aligned with design system
• Created comprehensive Jest test suites significantly improving code coverage and business logic reliability
• Provided technical leadership and mentorship to junior engineers, guiding apprenticeship progression toward front-end proficiency
• Facilitated architectural decision-making and technical refinement sessions in SCRUM ceremonies
• Drove adoption of TypeScript across full stack for type safety and improved maintainability
• Established CI/CD pipelines for automated testing and deployment

RESULTS:
• Successfully launched CRM platform to market within deadline
• Delivered scalable, event-sourced architecture ready for production workloads
• Established high code quality standards with comprehensive automated testing
• Developed junior engineers into productive front-end contributors
• Created reusable component library accelerating feature development
• Achieved high team velocity while maintaining technical excellence

IMPACT SUMMARY:
Led end-to-end architecture and market launch of scalable CRM SaaS platform as Tech Lead. Designed event-driven microservices using CQRS and event sourcing with NestJS and EventStore. Established front-end standards, championed testing practices, and mentored junior engineers to deliver production-ready platform within startup timelines.

CONDENSED VERSION:
