BACKGROUND CONTEXT:
When I joined, the TV advertising platform was in a critical state — a monolithic legacy stack powering millions of ad impressions per day, burdened by years of rapid feature growth without architectural discipline. Releases were risky, engineers were leaving due to system fragility, and business stakeholders were losing confidence. The leadership needed someone to stabilize delivery, reduce outages, and create an architectural path toward scalability and innovation. The business could not be stopped and features could not be stopped from being developed as a multitude of stakeholders were involved.

SITUATION:
High engineer turnover due to frustration with an obsolete legacy tech stack. The TV advertising platform's architecture was outdated, fragile, and unattractive for skilled developers, causing morale issues and loss of ownership.

TASK:
Understand the root causes of engineer dissatisfaction and rebuild engagement through modern technical practices, ownership culture, and innovation opportunities.

ACTIONS:
• Introduced a state-of-the-art cloud-native engineering stack featuring TypeScript, microservices, serverless functions, and event-driven onion architecture to replace legacy monolith components
• Refactored callback-heavy JavaScript into maintainable TypeScript code using async/await and promises for clarity and reliability
• Migrated complex application logic (e.g., state machine handling) to AWS Step Functions to offload orchestration from application code
• Implemented AWS EventBridge for event-driven decoupling to reduce interdependencies and eliminate single points of failure
• Created CI/CD pipelines and modern DevOps workflows, giving engineers autonomy and visibility in deployment processes

RESULTS:
• Engineer engagement and participation in product discussions increased significantly
• Voluntary turnover rate declined sharply
• Innovation culture revived — engineers began contributing ideas for both technical and business improvements

IMPACT SUMMARY:
Revitalized a disengaged engineering team by transforming legacy systems into a modern, cloud-native stack that restored ownership, motivation, and innovation across teams. Enhanced long-term retention and built a sustainable culture of technical excellence and collaboration.

CONDENSED VERSION:
Reduced engineer turnover and revived innovation by modernizing legacy AdTech systems. Introduced AWS serverless, microservices, and event-driven architecture using TypeScript and Step Functions. Improved engagement by giving engineers autonomy, ownership, and cutting-edge tools.

