r-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:126","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:142"],"citation":"Supported by event-sourced CRM platform launch, event-storming requirements shaping, CI/CD automation, and scalability architecture evidence at Daypaio; this strengthens the category’s greenfield-plus-brownfield pattern."}],"gap_analysis":[{"signal":"Architecture-first AI-architect headline and summary framing","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"This category wants architecture plus governed delivery at the top of the CV, and the current metadata does not surface that clearly.","current_state":"The current headline is 'Engineering Leader / Software Architect' and the summary foregrounds legacy modernization but omits the strongest governed AI workflow architecture evidence.","safe_interpretation":"The curated store supports a player-coach software architect with enterprise AI workflow, governance, reliability, and stakeholder-translation evidence; it does not require executive framing.","recommended_action":"Surface architect/player-coach scope plus enterprise AI workflow governance in the headline and summary, anchored in Commander-4 plus Seven.One modernization evidence.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:282","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9"],"citation":"Underrepresented in data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3 despite curated support for governed AI workflow delivery and architecture in Seven.One and Commander-4; category headline guidance explicitly prefers architecture-first, delivery-backed framing."},{"signal":"Current-role technical-architect title provenance","gap_type":"supported_upstream_pending_curation","why_it_matters":"Safe architect title family is easier to support when canonical metadata contains provenance-backed architect wording for the current role.","current_state":"Upstream knowledge-base records repeatedly label the current role as 'Lead Software Engineer / Technical Architect' or 'Technical Lead - Addressable TV', but canonical role metadata still exposes only 'Technical Lead (Addressable TV)'.","safe_interpretation":"A technical-architect descriptor appears well supported upstream, but it is not yet downstream-safe until promoted into curated metadata with provenance.","recommended_action":"Promote the architect-title variant into data/master-cv/role_metadata.json and current-role metadata, preserving provenance to knowledge-base records.","evidence_refs":["docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:7","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:98","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:181","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:268","docs/archive/knowledge-base.md:360","data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3"],"citation":"Not yet curated from multiple current-role STAR records in docs/archive/knowledge-base.md into canonical metadata; this directly affects safe use of the 'Solutions Architect / AI Architect' title family."},{"signal":"Greenfield 0→1 platform architecture and roadmap shaping","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"The sample explicitly rewards architects who can handle greenfield plus brownfield scope, and this candidate has both.","current_state":"Daypaio contains strong greenfield architecture, event-storming, CI/CD, and scalability evidence, but it is not surfaced in the current role-priority representation or summary.","safe_interpretation":"The candidate can safely claim prior greenfield platform architecture and roadmap translation experience without inflating it into enterprise-architect-wide scope.","recommended_action":"Elevate Daypaio’s 0→1 platform, event-storming, and scalability bullets into the master-CV’s top supporting roles for this category.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:27","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:44","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:126","data/master-cv/roles/02_samdock_daypaio.md:142"],"citation":"Supported by curated Daypaio evidence but underrepresented in the current master-CV priority ordering; category guidance prefers greenfield plus brownfield coverage."},{"signal":"Governed AI delivery language is too fragmented across projects and skills","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"This category is differentiated by governed agentic delivery, not by narrow retrieval-tool keywords alone.","current_state":"Commander-4 and Lantern prove guardrails, structured outputs, evaluation, observability, cost-aware routing, and access control, but the current representation leans heavily on retrieval stack details and tool names.","safe_interpretation":"The candidate can safely present governed enterprise AI workflow and LLM-gateway architecture with evaluation, access control, and production delivery.","recommended_action":"Compress narrow retrieval/tool detail and surface governance, evaluation, reliability, and workflow-orchestration outcomes in summary, projects, and skills.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:10"],"citation":"Underrepresented in current headline/summary/skills despite curated evidence of guardrails, access control, eval-driven gates, semantic caching, and production observability; category guidance prefers governed delivery over prompt-engineering or fine-tuning identity."},{"signal":"EEA-safe privacy and compliance delivery","gap_type":"curated_but_underrepresented","why_it_matters":"Privacy-aware delivery is optional but useful in this EEA category when supported narrowly and concretely.","current_state":"The curated store includes GDPR/TCF compliance delivery plus AI guardrails/access control, but the current representation does not connect them as a narrow governance-aware signal.","safe_interpretation":"The candidate can safely claim privacy/compliance-aware delivery experience and delivery controls; formal ownership of AI governance or regulatory programs remains too strong.","recommended_action":"Surface GDPR/TCF work once, paired with guardrails/access-control evidence, and avoid broader regulatory-program ownership language.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:106","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:332","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9"],"citation":"Supported by explicit GDPR/TCF compliance and guarded AI workflow controls, but currently absent from the representation layer; category guidance allows compliance terms only when directly evidenced and narrowly framed."},{"signal":"Formal people-management or executive-scope framing","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"This market penalizes inflated management framing when the evidence is primarily player-coach architect scope.","current_state":"The current headline starts with 'Engineering Leader', and the curated store includes mentorship and hiring-process evidence, but direct-report ownership and performance-management accountability are not established as dominant facts.","safe_interpretation":"Technical leadership, mentoring, architecture direction, and selective hiring participation are safe; formal people manager, director, or executive claims are not.","recommended_action":"De-emphasize manager/executive language in headline and summary and keep leadership wording tied to technical direction, mentoring, reviews, and stakeholder alignment.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217"],"citation":"Unsafe because the category is IC/player-coach heavy and only lightly rewards hiring/performance management; current evidence supports technical leadership better than formal management ownership."},{"signal":"Deep multi-cloud, model-training, or prompt-specialist framing","gap_type":"unsupported_or_unsafe","why_it_matters":"The category explicitly favors applied architecture and governed delivery over inflated cloud breadth or model-science claims.","current_state":"There is evidence for AWS architecture, Azure/OpenAI endpoint routing inside Lantern, and enterprise AI workflows, but no evidence for broad multi-cloud enterprise ownership or training/fine-tuning pipelines.","safe_interpretation":"Multi-provider LLM gateway and cloud-based platform work are safe; deep multi-cloud expert, fine-tuning, custom embedding training, RLHF, or prompt-specialist identity are not.","recommended_action":"Keep cloud claims narrow and preserve explicit exclusions from do-not-claim files.","evidence_refs":["data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:7","data/master-cv/projects/lantern.md:8","data/master-cv/projects/commander4.md:9","data/master-cv/projects/commander4_skills.json:42","data/master-cv/projects/lantern_skills.json:49"],"citation":"Unsafe because the evidence store explicitly excludes fine-tuning pipeline, custom embedding training, and RLHF, while category guidance warns against deep multi-cloud and prompt-engineering-centric framing without explicit proof."}],"safe_claims_now":{"headline_safe":["Software Architect / Technical Lead for enterprise platforms and AI workflows","Enterprise AI workflow and platform architecture with governance, evaluation, and production delivery","Player-coach architect for modernization, observability, and stakeholder-aligned delivery"],"profile_safe":["Translated business constraints, technical debt, and platform risk into architectural direction and delivery roadmaps.","Delivered governed AI workflow capabilities with guardrails, structured outputs, access control, retrieval evaluation, and LLM gateway patterns.","Combined brownfield modernization and prior greenfield platform work across event-driven, cloud-based systems."],"experience_safe":["Transformed a legacy AdTech platform into event-driven AWS microservices, reducing incidents by 75% and sustaining 3 years of zero downtime.","Served as platform lead for an internal enterprise AI workflow platform used by 2,000 users with 42 plugins, including evaluation harnesses, guardrail profiles, and per-silo access control.","Architected a 0→1 event-sourced CRM platform and supported market launch with scalable architecture, CI/CD automation, and requirements-shaping workshops.","Built observability, monitoring, and deployment patterns that improved release cadence, delivery predictability, and operational debugging."],"leadership_safe":["Mentored 10+ engineers on architecture and cloud patterns and helped grow 3 into lead positions.","Led stakeholder conversations on technical debt ROI, business metrics, and system risk under ambiguity.","Set architectural direction through DDD, bounded contexts, event-driven patterns, and north-star design."],"unsafe_or_too_weak":["Executive, director, head-of-function, or VP scope.","Formal line-management or performance-ownership framing.","Deep multi-cloud expert across all major cloud providers.","Fine-tuning pipeline, custom embedding training, RLHF, or research-led AI claims.","Power Platform, Copilot Studio, Purview, or DLP specialist claims.","Formal AI governance or regulatory-program ownership beyond evidenced delivery controls and GDPR/TCF implementation."],"citations":["data/master-cv/role_metadata.json:3","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:28","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:88","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:106","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:123","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:182","data/master-cv/roles/01_seven_one_entertainment.md:217","data/mast